HEADWORD: Wassailer
<hw>Was"sail*er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who drinks
wassail; one who engages in festivity, especially in drinking; a
reveler.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The rudeness and swilled insolence⟦br⟧
Of such late <qex>wassailers</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wast</ent>⟦br⟧
